  "homeQuickActionPurification": "Wudu & Ghusl",
  "purificationGuideTitle": "Wudu & Ghusl",
  "purificationGuideSubtitle": "Guide to ritual purification before prayer",
  "purificationGuideIntro": "Before salah, a Muslim may need ritual purification. The two main forms are wudu (minor ablution) and ghusl (full ritual bath). This guide explains what each one is, when it is needed, and how to perform it.",
  "purificationGuideWuduTitle": "Wudu",
  "purificationGuideWuduBody": "What it is:\nWudu is the minor ritual purification used before salah when major impurity is not present.\n\nWhen you need it:\n• Before prayer if you do not have a valid wudu.\n• After going to the bathroom.\n• After anything that breaks your state of purity, such as passing wind, deep sleep, or losing consciousness.\n\nSteps of wudu:\n1. Make the intention in your heart.\n2. Say \"Bismillah\".\n3. Wash both hands 3 times, usually starting with the right.\n4. Rinse the mouth 3 times.\n5. Clean the nose with water 3 times.\n6. Wash the whole face 3 times.\n7. Wash the arms to the elbows 3 times, starting with the right arm and then the left.\n8. Wipe the head once with wet hands.\n9. Wipe the ears once.\n10. Wash the feet to the ankles 3 times, starting with the right foot and then the left.\n\nImportant notes:\n• The usual practice is 3 times, but 1 time is enough for validity.\n• Make sure the water reaches the whole area properly.\n• Keep the correct order.\n• Avoid anything that blocks the water, such as dirt or a layer covering the skin.",
  "purificationGuideWuduWhatIsLabel": "What it is",
  "purificationGuideWuduWhatIsBody": "Wudu is the minor ritual purification before salah when major impurity is not present.",
  "purificationGuideWuduWhenNeededLabel": "When you need it",
  "purificationGuideWuduWhenNeededPrayer": "Before prayer if you do not have a valid wudu.",
  "purificationGuideWuduWhenNeededBathroom": "After going to the bathroom.",
  "purificationGuideWuduWhenNeededPurityLoss": "After losing your state of purity, such as by passing wind, deep sleep, or losing consciousness.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStepsTitle": "Steps of wudu",
  "purificationGuideWuduStepsSubtitle": "Usually each wash is done 3 times, though 1 time is enough for validity.",
  "purificationGuideWuduNotesTitle": "Important notes",
  "purificationGuideWuduNoteModeration": "Do not go beyond what is needed or turn the washing into a burden.",
  "purificationGuideWuduNoteWater": "Make sure the water reaches the whole area properly.",
  "purificationGuideWuduNoteOrder": "Keep the correct order from start to finish.",
  "purificationGuideWuduNoteObstacles": "Remove anything that blocks the water, such as dirt or a layer covering the skin.",
  "purificationGuideWuduRepeatOnce": "1 time",
  "purificationGuideWuduRepeatThreeTimes": "3 times",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep1Title": "Intention",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep1Body": "Make the intention in your heart to perform wudu for salah.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep2Title": "Bismillah",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep2Body": "Say Bismillah before beginning the washing.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep3Title": "Wash the hands",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep3Body": "Wash both hands thoroughly, usually beginning with the right.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep4Title": "Rinse the mouth",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep4Body": "Rinse the mouth well so the water reaches inside.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep5Title": "Clean the nose",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep5Body": "Draw water gently into the nose and clean it out.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep6Title": "Wash the face",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep6Body": "Wash the whole face, from forehead to chin and from ear to ear.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep7Title": "Wash the arms to the elbows",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep7Body": "Wash the right arm first, then the left, making sure the elbows are included.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep8Title": "Wipe the head",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep8Body": "Pass wet hands over the head gently from front to back.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep9Title": "Wipe the ears",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep9Body": "Wipe the ears with the same wetness, without needing extra water.",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep10Title": "Wash the feet to the ankles",
  "purificationGuideWuduStep10Body": "Wash the right foot first, then the left, making sure the ankles are included.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslTitle": "Ghusl",
  "purificationGuideGhuslBody": "What it is:\nGhusl is the full ritual bath. It is required after major impurity.\n\nWhen it is required:\n• After sexual relations.\n• After ejaculation.\n• After menstruation ends.\n• After postnatal bleeding ends.\n\nHow to do it:\n1. Make the intention in your heart.\n2. Say Bismillah.\n3. Wash the hands and private parts.\n4. Remove any visible impurity.\n5. Perform wudu.\n6. Pour water over the head so it reaches the scalp.\n7. Wash the whole body, starting with the right side and then the left, making sure water reaches every part.\n\nImportant note:\nA complete ghusl removes major impurity. If nothing happens afterwards to break wudu, you may pray without making a separate wudu again.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslWhatIsLabel": "What it is",
  "purificationGuideGhuslWhatIsBody": "Ghusl is the full ritual bath required after major impurity.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslWhenNeededLabel": "When you need it",
  "purificationGuideGhuslWhenNeededRelations": "After intimate relations.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslWhenNeededMenstruation": "After menstruation ends.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslWhenNeededPostnatal": "After postnatal bleeding ends.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslWhenNeededDischarge": "After sexual discharge.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStepsTitle": "Steps of ghusl",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStepsSubtitle": "Ghusl does not have a fixed number of repetitions like wudu. The important thing is that water reaches the whole body, though some parts may be washed more than once in the recommended way.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslValidityTitle": "Complete form and minimum valid form",
  "purificationGuideGhuslValidityRecommended": "The complete recommended form follows the Sunnah pattern step by step, with careful washing and order.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslValidityMinimum": "The minimum valid form is simple: make the intention and ensure water covers the whole body.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslNotesTitle": "Important notes",
  "purificationGuideGhuslNoteDrySpots": "Make sure no area is left dry.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslNoteScalp": "Ensure the water reaches the scalp well.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslNoteBarriers": "Remove anything that blocks the water, such as dirt or a layer on the skin.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslNoteSimplicity": "Do not make it unnecessarily complicated.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslBadgeEssential": "Essential",
  "purificationGuideGhuslBadgeRecommended": "Recommended",
  "purificationGuideGhuslBadgeUntilClean": "Until clean",
  "purificationGuideGhuslBadgeUsuallyThreeTimes": "Often 3 times",
  "purificationGuideGhuslBadgeNoFixedCount": "No fixed count",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep1Title": "Intention",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep1Body": "Make the intention in your heart to remove major impurity and perform ghusl.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep2Title": "Bismillah",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep2Body": "Say Bismillah before starting the washing.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep3Title": "Wash the hands",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep3Body": "Wash both hands well before moving to the rest of the body.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep4Title": "Wash the private parts and remove visible impurity",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep4Body": "Clean the private parts and remove any visible impurity until the area is clean.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep5Title": "Perform wudu",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep5Body": "Perform wudu, or at least its basic form, before washing the whole body.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep6Title": "Pour water over the head",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep6Body": "Pour water over the head and make sure it reaches the scalp. This is often done several times, such as 3.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep7Title": "Wash the whole body",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep7Body": "Wash the whole body, usually starting with the right side and then the left. There is no fixed number as long as the water reaches everywhere.",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep8Title": "Make sure the water reaches every part",
  "purificationGuideGhuslStep8Body": "Check carefully that no area stays dry, especially hidden or folded parts of the body.",
  "purificationGuideFinalNoteTitle": "Key difference",
  "purificationGuideFinalNoteBody": "Wudu is for minor impurity. Ghusl is for major impurity. If you only need wudu, ghusl is not required. If ghusl is required, wudu alone is not enough.",
